acceptOffer(bytes32).details: through this function a borrower can accept an existing offera UI should do an off-chain balance check on the lender side to make sure the call won't throw

params._offer: Identifier of the offer to be accepted

claimDeed(uint256).details: The current Deed owner can call this function if the Deed is expired or payed back

params._did: Deed ID of the deed to be claimed

constructor.details: establishes a connection with other pre-deployed componentsfor the set up to work both PWNDeed & PWNVault contracts have to called via `.setPWN(PWN.address)`

params._PWND: Address of the PWNDeed contract - defines Deed tokens
params._PWNV: Address of the PWNVault contract - holds assets

createDeed(address,uint8,uint32,uint256,.details: for UI integrations is this the function enabling creation of a new Deed token

params._assetAmount: Amount of an ERC20 or ERC1155 token || 0 in case of NFTs
params._assetCategory: Category of the asset - see { MultiToken.sol }
params._assetId: ID of an ERC721 or ERC1155 token || 0 in case the token doesn't have IDs

returns._0: a Deed ID of the newly created Deed

makeOffer(address,uint256,uint256,uint25.details: this is the function used by lenders to cast their offersthis function doesn't assume the asset is approved yet for PWNVaultthis function requires lender to have a sufficient balance

params._assetAmount: Amount of an ERC20 token to be offered as loan
params._did: ID of the Deed the offer should be bound to
params._toBePaid: Amount to be paid back by the borrower

returns._0: a hash of the newly created offer

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

repayLoan(uint256).details: the borrower can pay back the funds through this functionthe function assumes the asset (and amount to be paid back) to be returned is approved for PWNVaultthe function assumes the borrower has the full amount to be paid back in their account

params._did: Deed ID of the deed being paid back

revokeDeed(uint256).details: through this function the borrower can delete the Deed token given no offer was accepted

params._did: Deed ID specifying the concrete Deed

revokeOffer(bytes32).details: this is the function lenders can use to remove their offers on Deeds they are in the stage of getting offers

params._offer: Identifier of the offer to be revoked

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
